President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Arkansas due to severe storms, straight-line winds, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred from June 23 to June 24, 2019. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Madison, Newton, and Washington are eligible for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be eligible for federal funding. Jerry S. Thomas has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.